---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'key-differences', text: 'Key Differences', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'GeoBlue Review', href: '/providers/geoblue' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'Best US Expat Insurance', href: '/best/us-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Insurance Type', geoblue: 'Health insurance', safetywing: 'Travel medical' },
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', geoblue: true, safetywing: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', geoblue: true, safetywing: 'Emergency only' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', geoblue: 'Moderate', safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', geoblue: '12 mo wait', safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Conditions', geoblue: 'Underwriting', safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'Routine Care', geoblue: true, safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', geoblue: 'BCBS network', safetywing: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Maximum Coverage', geoblue: '$5M', safetywing: '$250K' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'age', header: 'Age' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { age: '30', geoblue: '$150-230/mo', safetywing: '$45-70/mo' },
  { age: '40', geoblue: '$200-310/mo', safetywing: '$65-95/mo' },
  { age: '50', geoblue: '$280-430/mo', safetywing: '$95-140/mo' },
  { age: '60', geoblue: '$400-620/mo', safetywing: '$150-210/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="GeoBlue vs SafetyWing"
  description="Compare GeoBlue and SafetyWing for US expats. Comprehensive BCBS coverage vs budget travel medical insurance."
  headline="GeoBlue vs SafetyWing"
  subheadline="Comprehensive health insurance vs budget travel medical. Very different products for different needs."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Options"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue and SafetyWing are fundamentally different products. GeoBlue is comprehensive health insurance with BCBS network access; SafetyWing is budget travel medical insurance for nomads. The comparison is between protection levels, not just price.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">GeoBlue</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Comprehensive health insurance</li>
        <li>BCBS network (1.7M+ providers)</li>
        <li>Covers routine and preventive care</li>
        <li>Pre-existing conditions (underwritten)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">SafetyWing</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Travel medical insurance</li>
        <li>Emergency coverage only</li>
        <li>No routine care coverage</li>
        <li>No pre-existing conditions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Important Distinction</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      These are not equivalent products. SafetyWing is travel medical insurance designed for emergencies. GeoBlue is comprehensive health insurance. Choosing SafetyWing to save money means accepting significant coverage gaps.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    The coverage differences are substantial. This isn't about minor feature variations—it's about fundamentally different protection levels.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p><strong>What SafetyWing doesn't cover:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions (completely excluded)</li>
    <li>Routine care, checkups, preventive care</li>
    <li>Mental health treatment</li>
    <li>Maternity (except emergency complications)</li>
    <li>Chronic condition management</li>
    <li>Dental (except emergency)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing costs 60-75% less than GeoBlue. But you're comparing travel insurance to health insurance—the savings reflect the coverage gap.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p><strong>What the price difference means:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>At 30: Save ~$100/mo but lose routine care, mental health, pre-existing coverage</li>
    <li>At 50: Save ~$185/mo but one health issue could cost thousands out-of-pocket</li>
    <li>The "savings" disappear if you need any non-emergency care</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="key-differences">Key Differences</h2>

  <h3>US Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Full BCBS network access—negotiated rates at 90% of US hospitals.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Limited US coverage with caps. Not designed for ongoing US care.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-term Viability</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Suitable for years of expat life. Lifetime renewal available.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Designed for temporary travel. Not ideal for permanent expats.
  </p>

  <h3>Risk Profile</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Comprehensive protection against health costs.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Emergency-only coverage. Significant financial risk for non-emergencies.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose GeoBlue If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're a US citizen living abroad long-term</li>
        <li>You have any health conditions</li>
        <li>You want routine care covered</li>
        <li>You need mental health coverage</li>
        <li>You visit the US regularly</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">SafetyWing May Work If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're young and very healthy</li>
        <li>You're traveling short-term (under 1 year)</li>
        <li>You have zero health conditions</li>
        <li>You understand and accept the coverage gaps</li>
        <li>Budget is absolutely critical</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    For US citizens planning to live abroad long-term, GeoBlue is the responsible choice. The BCBS network access alone justifies the premium for anyone who may need US care.
  </p>
  <p>
    SafetyWing can work for young, healthy digital nomads on short-term adventures who understand they're buying emergency coverage only. But calling it a substitute for health insurance is misleading.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>The real question:</strong> Can you afford to pay out-of-pocket for routine care, mental health, and any pre-existing conditions? If not, SafetyWing's "savings" are illusory.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Proper Coverage"
    description="Compare comprehensive health insurance options."
    buttonText="See All Options"
    buttonHref="/best/us-expat-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance, not comprehensive health insurance. Understand the coverage limitations before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
